<!doctype html>
<html>
    <head>
        <title>Continuous Testing Form</title>
        <link rel="stylesheet" href="projPage.css">
        <script src="https://ajax.googleapis.com/ajax/libs/angularjs/1.4.9/angular.min.js"></script>
        <meta charset="utf-8">
        <meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=edge">
        <title>Scoreboard Hackathon</title>
        <link rel="stylesheet" href="projPage.css">
        <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
        <link rel="stylesheet" href="http://maxcdn.bootstrapcdn.com/bootstrap/3.3.7/css/bootstrap.min.css">
        <script src="https://ajax.googleapis.com/ajax/libs/jquery/1.12.4/jquery.min.js"></script>
        <script src="http://maxcdn.bootstrapcdn.com/bootstrap/3.3.7/js/bootstrap.min.js"></script>
    </head>
    <body>
        <nav class="navbar navbar-static-top navbar-light bg-faded">
              <a href="/projPage" class="navbar-brand">BAH Hackathon</a>
              <ul class="nav navbar-nav">
                  <li class="nav-item">
                      <a class="nav-link" href="/login">Login</a>
                  </li>
             </ul>
        </nav>
        <div ng-app="myApp" ng-controller="myCtrl" id="app"></div>
        <div class="jumbotron">
            <div class="container">
                <h1 class="display-3">Testing Criteria</h1>
                <p>The following questions should be asked about each of the ensuing test types. Is the test implemented? How is it implemented? Is it an effective implementation?</p>
            </div>
        </div>
            <center>
            <p id="hackathonName">
            <script>getHackathonName()</script>
            </p>
            
            <p id="teamName">
                <script>getTeamName()</script>
            </p>
            
            <p id="projectName">
            <script>getProjectName()</script></p>
            </center>  
        <br><br>
         <div class="col-md-12">
             <p style="text-center;">
            <p id="criteriaDetails">

            The following questions should be asked about each of the ensuing test types. Is the test implemented? How is it implemented? Is it an effective implementation? </p>
            <br>

            <b>Unit testing </b>
                <br>
            <b>Performance testing</b>
                <br>
            <b>Static code analysis</b>
                <br>
            <b>Integration testing</b>
                <br>
            <b>Continous testing</b>: did teams expand upon the CI pipeline to include continuous testing? Did they add tools like TestNG and Selenium to Jenkins? When does this testing occur? After each commit? Or manually?
           
                </p>
            <br>




            </p>
            <form id="judgeForm" action="/scoreboard" method="get">
                Rating: 
                <select name="rating:">
                <option value="0">0</option>
                <option value="1">1</option>
                 <option value="2">2</option>
                    <option value="3">3</option>
                    <option value="4">4</option>
                    <option value="5">5</option>
                </select>
                <br><br>
                Feedback:
                <textarea id="continuousTestingFeedback" rows="5" cols="30"></textarea>
                <br><br>
                <input type="submit" value="Save and Submit" onclick="redirect();">
                </form>
        </div>
    </body>
</html>